Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.52,0:00:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,In the quiet countryside, next to a lake, \Nthere's a summer camp. {.on the quiet lake shore}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.42,0:00:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, who came here for her summer vacations
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.00,0:00:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly meets another girl, Lotte, \Nlooking exactly like her.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.25,0:00:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Denial was her first reaction. {opposition; rebellion; revolt; resistance; backlash; refusal}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.20,0:00:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Between the two girls, who had never exchanged \Na word before, a bizarre sentiment suddenly arises.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.07,0:00:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The two are probably yet to realize -
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.77,0:00:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it was the most fateful meeting of their lives. {/it was a fateful meeting}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.18,0:00:33.15,Sign,,0,0,115,,{\c&HDCE8F4&\3c&H1C2C0E&\bord0\blur1}Episode 2 \N {\fs50} Thread of Fate{運命の糸}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.57,0:01:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.35,0:01:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Today it's certainly going to be fun, too. {/will become funny as well}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.14,0:01:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No way she gives in. \NNot to some Munich snob girl. {/she won't lose, not to some munich broad}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.96,0:02:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Luise. \NLet's go play over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.50,0:02:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, I got a ball! \NBrigitte let me borrow it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.84,0:02:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That miser girl did? Can't believe my ears! {kashita is actually another word for "to loan" but they actually said it before so what's the point of repeating}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.61,0:02:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, maybe we do dodgeball?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.96,0:02:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina, we'll be needing this court to play dodgeball now, \Nyou go use some other place for chatting.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.37,0:02:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's have our leave, girls. {/let's go}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.07,0:02:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They are still just as uncommunicative to each other. {/as always, don't exchange any words}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.73,0:02:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, Luise and Lotte \Nare not starting to get along any time soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.07,0:02:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This morning, we never saw one \Nkicking another's leg, didn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.53,0:02:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, they are so strikingly similar, \Nit's as though they are astrological twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.29,0:02:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Astrological twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.92,0:02:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,When people look absolutely alike, \Nwithout being even distantly related,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.07,0:02:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,most likely, they just happened to be born \Nin the same fraction of the same second.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.96,0:03:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,This reminds me of some older story I've read...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.53,0:03:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a tailor in London
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.32,0:03:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,who looked exactly like Edward VII, the King of England. \NYou couldn't tell them apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.39,0:03:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And they had actually been born in the same second?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.46,0:03:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.23,0:03:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.64,0:03:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,At the King's behest, the tailor had to shave off his beard \Nto differ from the King. {/his beard exactly like the king's}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.32,0:03:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But still, what do we do about those girls?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.55,0:03:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't make one shave off her beard.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.95,0:03:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,They will be just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.95,0:03:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,While in their souls, \Nthe sentiment of rebuke still predominates, {/they feel like rebelling/opposing/denying, yet at the same time}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.58,0:03:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the sentiment of attraction \Nis soon to displace it. {/the feeling of pulling also supposed to be there}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.16,0:03:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, let's do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.68,0:03:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on? \NYou're not being your usual self.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.22,0:03:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's that energy you always have in you? {/what happened to your usual genki}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.01,0:03:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,True! The always tireless Luise \Nis just indifferent instead. {/w/o being to be in high spirits; to be full of vigor (vigour); to be enthusiastic; to be eager; to stretch to breaking point, you're just bored/uninterested}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.54,0:03:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Think I'll pass today. {/enough already/stop}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.60,0:03:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.42,0:04:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You're being weird since yesterday, Luise
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.36,0:04:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it because of this Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.55,0:04:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let her get under your skin! {/if it bothers you so much,}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.01,0:04:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, just hurry up and bite off her nose already!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.38,0:04:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you stop saying such rubbish, Christine? {/I can't do such stupid thing}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.48,0:04:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But I thought she is going to reap \Nthe full extent of your anger! {/weren't you so much mad at her} {I tled this as "earned your anger"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.59,0:04:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't go around biting off everybody's noses \Njust cause they anger me one way or another.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.38,0:04:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. \NIt wouldn't be reasonable. {/I can't do such thing}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.11,0:04:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that talk? \NI was just trying to put myself in your shoes. {/I said it as if your emotions were mine}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.72,0:04:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You've never been in my shoes! {/You don't understand my feeling}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.81,0:04:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, Lotte never earned my anger in the first place! {/I'm not mad at lotte or something}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.36,0:04:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Fiddles, you were glowing with anger! {/became extremely angry; furious; enraged​}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.02,0:04:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And while we were dining, \Nyou kicked that girl in the shin!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.18,0:04:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, she nearly broke into tears then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.23,0:04:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone like Stephie would have cried right away. {/if it were stephie you kicked, she'd definitely cry}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.28,0:04:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But Lotte is too boring for that. {/is a little thickheaded; insensitive; dull; thick-skinned}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.53,0:04:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough I said!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.59,0:04:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't shut up at once, \Nyou'll be the ones getting a kick on the shins next! {not really sure what she means by "if you say even more funny things of that kind, I'll kick you"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.05,0:04:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.76,0:04:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the usual Luise we know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.89,0:04:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I really wonder what's gotten into you, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.93,0:05:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.02,0:05:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.06,0:05:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Want one?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.27,0:05:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you be willing to put it on my head?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.07,0:06:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Lovely! It looks great on you. {/pretty, it totally fits/becoming you}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.70,0:06:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.55,0:06:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But aren't you still mad at me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.13,0:06:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You were the only one mad at people!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.70,0:06:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it came as a surprise. {/I was startled}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.39,0:06:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You appearing so suddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.17,0:06:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a little started myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.79,0:06:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you leg hurt bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.45,0:06:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,A bit, yes. Nobody ever kicked me like that before. {/in that way/method/manner}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.78,0:06:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I yielded to my habit. \NSlapping people here and there... {/I do that often - to slap; to strike; to spank}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.72,0:06:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You're such a {great }tomboy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.60,0:06:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.88,0:06:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot already.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.43,0:06:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, don't you think it's really peculiar?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.26,0:06:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What's peculiar? {not really sure what she means "you say okashi?"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.94,0:06:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you know... {/after all}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.88,0:06:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.95,0:06:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, you have any siblings?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.74,0:07:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I have none.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.62,0:07:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So do I!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.86,0:07:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.27,0:07:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I know! Luise, would you mind \Nsitting here for a moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.88,0:07:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.36,0:07:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Bear with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.95,0:07:37.05,Sign,,0,0,0,,You always yell like that \Nwhen your mom combs your hair, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.05,0:07:39.27,Sign,,0,0,0,,But I don't really have a mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.71,0:07:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.96,0:07:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.08,0:07:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, that's why \NI'm being so noncompliant sometimes. {1. noisy; loud; boisterous; clamorous; raucous​\NI-adjective (keiyoushi)\N2. turbulent; unsettled; restless child}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.15,0:07:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That explains a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.35,0:07:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It feels like they've never been brushed before.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.67,0:07:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you're just too used to your mom \Nalways combing your hair for you? {/is lotte's mom always ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.46,0:07:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true that she's been doing it \Nsince I was small. {Always.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.89,0:07:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But these days, I do it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.84,0:07:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom is being too busy with her work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.35,0:08:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And dad... Well I don't have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.85,0:08:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We are such a polar opposites. {/it's the opposite for us}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.33,0:08:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,In my family, it's dad who is constantly busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.77,0:08:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He is a musician.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.19,0:08:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes, he composes, \Nsometimes he conducts operas. {/as a composer and as a conductor in opera}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.69,0:08:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Also living with us - \Nour housekeeper Resi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.57,0:08:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,She's nice and all, but combing a child's hair \Nis not something she's fond of.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.91,0:08:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't your dad ever take a slipper to you? {/spank your ass}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.06,0:08:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you serious? {/no way}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.20,0:08:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,My dad dotes on me too much, saying this all the time: \N"You are my most precious treasure!"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.26,0:08:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Even when I do something deserving scolding, \Nhe just looks me straight in the eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.87,0:08:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and asks me this, ever so seriously: {/slowly/patiently to tell; to (try to) persuade; to advise; to warn; to admonish; to reason}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.00,0:08:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,"Are you asking for a spanking?" {unsure what she means by "I'm not going to hit anywhere or something else."}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.91,0:08:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,My! So he spoiled you beyond belief.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.21,0:08:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all! It's just that my dad \Nis always preoccupied with other stuff he has to tend to. {hope this is what she means by "dad always has hid head full of thoughts"}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.85,0:08:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But can't he free up \Neven just one hand to do it? {/one hand would be enough for that, after all}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.21,0:08:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't recognize our Luise. {/... is weird isn't she}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.69,0:08:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,She's not here either. \NWhere else could she be?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.12,0:08:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget about her. {/leave ... alone}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.14,0:08:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,She can't make up her mind herself! {/She's out of her mind.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.76,0:09:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.66,0:09:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Like two beans in a pod!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.89,0:09:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't tell one from another myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.46,0:09:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Lotte, you have another apron like that? {/is this the only ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.51,0:09:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a spare one in the bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.88,0:09:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Sublime! You mind if I borrow it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.00,0:09:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No, don't mind at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.94,0:09:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.49,0:09:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This smells like tons of fun! \NI can't wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.07,0:09:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Where could those two be?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.20,0:09:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Wherever they are, \NI bet they are fighting to death. {/having a duel; shoot-out}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.33,0:09:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we'll see a full-blown slap{ on the cheeks} this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.17,0:09:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be such a waste if she does it \Nwhile we're not watching! {hope this is what she means by "if she does such interesting thing behind one's back/in the shadows, I won't forgive her"}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.07,0:09:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Christine, she's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.48,0:09:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you! This there is Luise's seat!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.11,0:09:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Asking for another kick, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.91,0:10:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What in the world is going on? \NWhich one is the real Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.23,0:10:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, how do we ever tell which one is you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.51,0:10:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,She is from Munich! {guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.76,0:10:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if there's ever a third one \Nlooking exactly like this! {also half-guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.86,0:10:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you gotta be kidding me! \NYou were like cat and dog just yesterday! {/fighting until recently}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.92,0:10:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,How did it come to this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.69,0:10:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What's all this commotion about?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.45,0:11:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What exactly is going on here? Pray, try to explain, Lotte. \NOh no, is Lotte the one over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.18,0:11:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, why is this happening? \NI'm going mad. {/don't understand}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.87,0:11:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,My, my! Your resemblance is so remarkable, \Nit is now bordering a mischief?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.31,0:11:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You're such a troublesome bunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.44,0:11:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But still, won't you tell us just to be sure, \Nwhich one is Luise Palfy and which one is Lotte Körner?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.54,0:11:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.92,0:11:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying? \NThis transgress an innocuous joke, you two. {/you should stop joking}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.88,0:11:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, aren't we in trouble now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.89,0:11:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,How should we ever tell you apart? {/what should we do after this}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.87,0:11:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Girls, can anyone here distinguish them? {/anyone knows}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.69,0:11:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Truda can! Truda, if there's anyone \Nwho could, it must be you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.00,0:11:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You spend your whole life in the same class as Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.71,0:11:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh, you think so? {/no way}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.65,0:11:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't see a difference. At all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.75,0:11:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it! There's a surefire way \Nto tell apart at least one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.88,0:11:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.79,0:11:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This here is Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.09,0:11:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This girl sure knows what she's doing! {/no doubt about this girl}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.98,0:12:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,My, how most unexpected!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.72,0:12:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That can be considered sorted out. {hope it's hitosawagase - person that annoys or causes trouble; false alarm}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.46,0:12:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now, everyone. \NReturn to your seats.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.85,0:12:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We can postpone the discussion to after the lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.84,0:12:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you plan to dress up like this every day now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.82,0:12:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No way! Those braids are too burdensome to wear. {/This sober hair style imposes a certain strain upon me.} {/constraining  - 1. narrow; tight; cramped​\NNa-adjective (keiyodoshi), Noun\N2. formal; stiff; strict; ceremonious; rigid​\NNa-adjective (keiyodoshi), Noun\N3. constrained; uncomfortable}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.08,0:12:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Minding your conduct, \Nlike a proper braided girl would, is above me! {to behave well; to mind one's manners​ is against my nature}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.70,0:12:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Some things in Luise never change, after all. {/that is very louise-like}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.89,0:12:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,My! Not a hint of consideration for others' feelings! {/I want you to consider/think of people's trouble; bother; annoyance; nuisance; inconvenience}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.03,0:12:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You swore your eternal enmity just yesterday, \Nand now you bring her along like we don't mean business! {/were so mad yesterday, to go along with; to follow someone's lead; to accompany someone; to compromise we are like fools aren't we - unsure if she means "you make us look idiots by hanging out with her/bringing her along" or "by hanging out with us, looking like her" or "you make yourself look stupid by hanging out with us" either way I'm not sure where "we" belongs here}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.84,0:12:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,My bad, my bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.86,0:12:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope we can become friends now, Truda. {/will start getting along after this}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.88,0:12:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope so too, Lotte. At least, I shouldn't be afraid of you\Nslapping me any given moment. {/I don't mind it}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.31,0:12:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Christine, how about us two \Nalso bury the hatchet and move on? {/forget about the fight we had}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.69,0:12:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure thing, you make friends where you find them. {/let's get along}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.86,0:13:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll tell me all about how Vienna is like, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.75,0:13:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Only as long as you reveal to me every secret of Munich!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.21,0:13:12.31,Sign,,0,0,0,,A photographer?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.77,0:13:15.89,Sign,,0,0,0,,Yes, we have one. \NBut why would you need him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.89,0:13:18.75,Sign,,0,0,0,,We wish to fix our "doubleness" by a camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.75,0:13:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll send the pictures back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.30,0:13:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Just letters would never suffice. {/with just letters, you totally can't understand}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.97,0:13:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact the two can be so alike - \Nyou wouldn't believe it until you see a picture!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.69,0:13:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. You want your relatives to see it, too? {/people at home}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.12,0:13:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. \NYou two can go down to the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.08,0:13:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.38,0:13:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure to take a great picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.47,0:13:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, you should be back by dinner. {/until evening}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.78,0:13:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.89,0:13:55.58,Sign,,0,0,0,,Seebühl Village
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.82,0:14:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Get ready now, young ladies. \NWe're starting.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.39,0:14:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Twin Frauleins, please straighten up your backs. {no clue what is that "au/ai"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.54,0:14:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The photo is done, \Ngood job, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.58,0:14:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Herr Eipeldauer. {German version, Appeldauer in english one}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.51,0:14:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,When will the picture be ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.43,0:14:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me just three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.92,0:14:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll format it into a postcard. {I think he means "I'll produce it in a form usually used for picture postcards"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.42,0:14:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we'll come pick it up later.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.97,0:14:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll make sure you'll love this print! {/to make a good picture}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.28,0:14:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, two young Frauleins on it \Nare as similar as twins!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.39,0:14:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He said "twins!"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.60,0:14:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, it's not every day \Nthat you get to see two girls so alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.27,0:15:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I'll send a few glossy prints \Nto some of the big illustrated magazines.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.24,0:15:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They're often interested in things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.59,0:15:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's better. \NI can finally feel like I am myself again. {/so refreshing, after all, I'm better this way}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.60,0:15:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, those pictures sure are expensive, \NI was startled by that tag. {/it was surprisingly pricey}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.02,0:15:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you worry about it. {/you can leave this to me}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.81,0:15:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad sent me here with a hefty allowance. {/dad gave me a lot of pocket money}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.98,0:15:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, aren't you thirsty? {/is your throat dry}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.69,0:15:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get something to drink here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.50,0:15:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.02,0:15:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be shy. I'll take care of you. \NJust a small detour, we'll be fine. {/leave this to me, dropping in on the way; stopping off at; making a side trip, ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.65,0:15:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, has your dad been dead for long?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.01,0:15:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.73,0:15:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.37,0:16:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom also never mentions my dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.20,0:16:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And the last time I was pressing her to tell me, \Nit was just too distressing for her. {/when before I persistently was asking, she made a very sad face}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.10,0:16:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So I no longer try to find out. {/now I don't ask}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.95,0:16:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But I shouldn't think that he is really dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.22,0:16:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never been to his grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.76,0:16:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I also don't have a single memory of my mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.75,0:16:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We used to have a photo of her, though. \NOn the piano in my dad's office.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.93,0:16:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All I can remember is that she was pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.50,0:16:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was small, \NI was looking at her all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.70,0:16:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, some years ago, \NI asked dad directly, {really unsure what she means by itkutsunotoki}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.01,0:16:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,"Where is my mom now?"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.23,0:16:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad never gave me an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.84,0:16:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Next day, the photo was gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.99,0:16:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he locked it up somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.37,0:16:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We're both so unfortunate. {hope this is what she means "it's not going well"}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.18,0:16:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,One doesn't have a dad \Nand the other doesn't have a mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.89,0:16:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, along with appearances, \Nwe suffer a common fate as well. {/not only our faces, but our circumstances; environment; situation are similar too}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.91,0:16:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably, age, too. \NYou're ten, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.89,0:16:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Will turn eleven on the fourteenth of October.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.51,0:16:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Fourteenth of October?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.19,0:16:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, this is my birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.08,0:17:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Mine, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.34,0:17:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And your birthplace is... {/where were you born}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.13,0:17:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Linz on the Danube.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.74,0:17:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Mine, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.35,0:17:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,My mom's name is Luiselotte Körner!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.61,0:17:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Luiselotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.02,0:17:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.52,0:17:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.88,0:17:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,A photo... \NI have mom's photo in my locker!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.68,0:17:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Show it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.69,0:17:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey! Is it epidemic among kids these days? {/is this a fashion; trend; vogue; craze; fad; popularity lately/these days?}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.12,0:17:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Drinking the juice and leaving without paying...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.64,0:18:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.94,0:18:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Hey! Your change!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.31,0:18:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what another mischief \Nare those young monkeys up to now? {taking the translation from book, because I have no clue what she means by "those idiots, I wonder what badness did they do/mischief"}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.34,0:18:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We're in trouble, Frau Muthesius!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.89,0:18:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Those girls are actually not astrological twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.56,0:18:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Please take a look at this register.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.42,0:18:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise and Lotte \Nwere really born on the same day!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.41,0:18:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It simply cannot be a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.25,0:18:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's what I had concluded, too, Fraulein Ulrica.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.08,0:18:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, you knew this already?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.11,0:18:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,After writing down Lotte's birthday, \NI immediately compared it to Luise's in the register. {/after listening to lotte's story, I compared it to record on louse in the register - unsure what exactly she means by that, she didn't really tell any story to speak of}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.45,0:18:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, what do we do about this? {unsure what she means by "why/how/what at this rate/in this fashion"}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.43,0:18:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, those two are yet to notice it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.62,0:18:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,They said they'll take a picture together \Nand send it home.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.61,0:18:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If that helps to unravel the knot, \Nall's well and good. {/it would be good if this helps to unravel/solve/untie the thread of mystery}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.30,0:19:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,However, as mere bystanders, you and me \Nshould limit our long-term interference in their fates. {/refrain from playing a role in their fates/serve as agents of destiny}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.78,0:19:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, Fraulein Ulrica?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.72,0:19:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.44,0:19:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,My mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.41,0:19:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Our{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.26,0:19:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.82,0:20:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means \Nwe really are sisters, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.41,0:20:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise and Lotte had finally discovered \Nthe thread of fate that binds them together. {/connects to each other}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.86,0:20:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,However, that thread is long \Nand is still lavishly knotty along the way. {/seems to be complexly/difficultly intertwined/entangles}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.83,0:20:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,How would the two \Nproceed with unraveling this thread further on? {/the two will start ... from now on}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.21,0:20:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, in a way distinctive to them only? {/... in an unprecedented manner}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.47,0:20:24.47,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.41,0:20:33.94,Sign,,0,0,0,,A miserable Romance {可哀想ね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.94,0:20:37.40,Sign,,0,0,0,,A tear-jerking nuance {涙誘うニュアンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.40,0:20:41.12,Sign,,0,0,0,,If you turn another page of your memories, {想い出のページめくれば}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.12,0:20:44.03,Sign,,0,0,0,,Here she is - heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン} {actually, "the heroine of the recollections" but that doesn't have a nice ring to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.25,0:20:55.67,Sign,,0,0,0,,I raise my eyes to your face - {あなたの面影　見上げて咲いている}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.67,0:20:59.43,Sign,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, I'm in full bloom {unsure, maybe "it's flourishing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.43,0:21:02.97,Sign,,0,0,0,,A sunflower amidst the blizzard - {act. in the middle of winter}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.97,0:21:06.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,that would be me, my dear {真冬のひまわり　それが私なの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.81,0:21:09.54,Sign,,0,0,0,,Always on the verge of freezing, {凍えるような気持ちでいつも}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.39,0:21:12.94,Sign,,0,0,0,,My feelings are out of control -
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.94,0:21:17.49,Sign,,0,0,0,,Too stiff to even say "Do you still love me?" {「好き?」と尋くこともできず}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.49,0:21:21.64,Sign,,0,0,0,,My lips just keep wavering in this wind! {風に揺れていたわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.19,0:21:26.84,Sign,,0,0,0,,A pitiful Romance {いじらしいね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.84,0:21:30.25,Sign,,0,0,0,,Something that only happens in dreams: {夢のような出来事}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.25,0:21:33.88,Sign,,0,0,0,,Trying hard to forget, I fell even more in love {忘れるために愛したの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.88,0:21:36.65,Sign,,0,0,0,,with heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.70,0:21:41.47,Sign,,0,0,0,,Miracle that I came across now is hugging me tight {めぐりあえた奇跡　そっと抱きしめて}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.47,0:21:44.88,Sign,,0,0,0,,This is the story of my life, I'll do my best to protect it! {私だけの歴史　守ってゆくわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.47,0:21:48.47,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.48,0:21:50.00,Sign,,0,0,0,,In the next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.74,0:21:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.21,0:21:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And I am Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.41,0:21:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Lotte, did you know \Nthat Stephie's parents are getting a divorce?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.57,0:22:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. They have already started the hearings \Nto decide, which parent she is staying with. {/trials}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.85,0:22:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's cruel, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.12,0:22:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,While sending Stephie away for summer vacations, \Ndoing such a thing behind her back!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.87,0:22:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor Stephie!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.49,0:22:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if we would ever be able to understand \Nthe feelings overflowing her now!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.79,0:22:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time in I and Myself: \NOath by the Lake. Don't miss it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.98,0:22:18.32,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 3\NOath by the Lake {湖の誓い} \N\N\N\N\N\N \h {\bord\blur0.8\fs20\c&HE3CDD8&\1a&H10&\3c&H767E27&}Translated by Perevodildo | Timings by Sub-RoRo 
